---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="HAP - Human authorization for consequential AI actions">

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       1. HERO
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">Open-Source Protocol · v0.5</p>
      <h1><span class="hl">Human authorization</span> <br class="desktop-break">for consequential AI actions.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        AI agents carry no authority of their own. Before an agent moves money,
        changes records, sends communication, grants access, or touches infrastructure,
        the action must receive a signed pre-execution receipt linked to human authorization.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="/protocol" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Protocol</a>
        <button type="button" id="copy-spec" class="btn btn-secondary" data-src="/context.txt">Copy for your AI</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       3. NO RECEIPT. NO EXECUTION.
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">The core invariant</p>
      <h2>No receipt. No execution.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        The receipt is not a post-execution log. It is the precondition for execution —
        and the audit artifact proving the action was authorized before it ran.
      </p>

      <div class="invariant-cols">
        <div class="receipt" role="figure" aria-label="Execution receipt example">
          <div class="receipt-head">
            Execution receipt
            <span class="receipt-tag">signed · pre-execution</span>
          </div>
          <dl class="receipt-fields">
            <dt class="rf-key">decision_owner</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">did:eudi:at:9f21… <span class="rf-note">— authorizing human, via attestation</span></dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">profile</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">charge@0.5</dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">bounds_hash</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">sha256:7a91…</dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">action_type</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">refund</dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">execution</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">order #4821 · €48.00</dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">cumulative</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">€391 / €500 today <span class="rf-note">— AS-tracked</span></dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">issued</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">2026-05-23T14:22Z</dd>
            <dt class="rf-key">signature</dt>
            <dd class="rf-val">ed25519:8f3b…1b4c</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>

        <ol class="chain">
          <li>A human authorizes <strong>bounded execution</strong> — scope, limits, time, and commitment mode.</li>
          <li>The <span class="role">Gatekeeper</span> verifies the attestation, checks per-action bounds, and enforces local context constraints.</li>
          <li>The <span class="role">Authority Server</span> checks cumulative limits, expiry, and revocation, then <strong>signs the receipt</strong>.</li>
          <li>The <span class="role">Executor</span> runs the action — only <strong>after</strong> the receipt exists.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <p class="neutrality">
        <strong>Open infrastructure.</strong> Any compliant Authority Server can
        issue receipts — Suveren is one implementation. The protocol is open;
        no single vendor owns the trust layer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       4. WHERE IT FITS
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec sec-alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">Where it fits</p>
      <h2>HAP composes. It doesn't compete.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        HAP isn't another login, API gateway, or agent framework. It's the layer that
        decides whether an already-reachable capability may be used for a
        <strong>consequential action</strong> — with proof.
      </p>

      <table class="contrast">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Layer</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="old">OAuth / OpenID Connect</td><td class="old">Grants API access</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="old">MCP</td><td class="old">Exposes tools to agents</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="old">Identity (EUDI, passkeys, WebAuthn)</td><td class="old">Proves who you are</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="hap">HAP</td><td class="hap">Authorizes the consequential action — before it runs, with a signed receipt</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p class="couplet"><span class="a">OAuth grants reachable capability.</span> <span class="b">HAP governs authorized use of that capability.</span></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       5. COMMITMENT MODES
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">Commitment modes</p>
      <h2>You decide how much runs on its own.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        The level of autonomy is a signed choice on every authorization — the
        protocol's <strong>commitment mode</strong>, not a default the agent can change.
      </p>

      <div class="modes">
        <div>
          <div class="mode-name">Automatic<span class="who">Agent runs within bounds</span></div>
          <p>The agent acts within the bounds you set. No per-action approval — the
            Authority Server enforces the limits and issues a signed receipt for each
            action before execution.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="mode-name">Review<span class="who">You approve each action</span></div>
          <p>The agent proposes; you approve each action before it runs.
            No approval, no receipt — no execution.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="mode-name">Review above a cap<span class="who">Approvers sign above a limit</span></div>
          <p>The agent runs on its own under a limit you set. Above it, the action
            routes to a named set of approvers before any receipt is issued.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       6. THE DISTINCTION
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec sec-alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">The distinction</p>
      <h2>Agents aren't employees. They're executors.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        Most systems give agents their own accounts, credentials, and standing
        permissions — one more identity to manage. HAP does the opposite.
      </p>
      <p>
        An agent never carries authority of its own. A human authorizes a bounded
        action; the <strong>receipt</strong> is cryptographic proof that this specific
        action was authorized — and issued before it ran. An agent may have technical
        identifiers for logging and routing, but it holds no <strong>independent authority</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="soul">
        As AI systems become more capable, HAP keeps authority from quietly
        moving from humans into machines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       7. TWO MODELS FOR AI AUTHORITY
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">The model choice</p>
      <h2>Two models for authorizing agents.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        How a system treats agent authority is an architectural decision with
        long-term governance consequences.
      </p>

      <table class="contrast">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Agent-identity approach</th>
            <th>HAP approach</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="old">Treat agents as authority-bearing actors</td>
            <td class="hap">Treat agents as executors</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="old">Manage standing agent permissions</td>
            <td class="hap">Issue bounded action receipts</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="old">Rely on accounts and credentials</td>
            <td class="hap">Bind execution to human authorization</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="old">Audit after execution</td>
            <td class="hap">Verify the receipt before execution</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="old">Agent acts under standing authority</td>
            <td class="hap">Agent acts only inside receipt-approved bounds</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="a14">
        <p class="label">EU AI Act — Article 14</p>
        <p>
          Article 14 requires effective human oversight of high-risk AI. HAP turns
          that oversight into an <strong>enforceable control at the action layer</strong>:
          consequential actions cannot run unless a human-linked authorization receipt
          exists before execution.
        </p>
        <p class="caveat">
          HAP is Article-14-enabling infrastructure — not compliance on its own.
          Compliance still requires governance, training, documentation, and human
          competence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       8. USE CASES
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec sec-alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">Use cases</p>
      <h2>Where consequential actions need proof.</h2>
      <div class="usecases">
        <div>Payments<span>refunds, charges, payouts</span></div>
        <div>Email<span>high-stakes sends</span></div>
        <div>CRM<span>record changes &amp; deletes</span></div>
        <div>Infrastructure<span>deploys &amp; config</span></div>
        <div>Multi-owner approvals<span>two people must sign</span></div>
        <div>Compliance audit<span>verifiable receipts</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       10. OPEN INFRASTRUCTURE
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="label">Open infrastructure</p>
      <h2>No single vendor owns the trust layer.</h2>
      <p class="body-lead">
        HAP is an open standard — MIT-licensed, developed in the open, and maintained
        by stewards, not owners. Any compliant Authority Server can issue receipts.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="/protocol" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Protocol</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/humanagencyprotocol/hap-protocol" class="btn btn-secondary">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Copy the full protocol context (/context.txt) to the clipboard for pasting into an AI chat.
  const btn = document.getElementById('copy-spec') as HTMLButtonElement | null;
  if (btn) {
    const original = btn.textContent;
    btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      try {
        const res = await fetch(btn.dataset.src || '/context.txt');
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(await res.text());
        btn.textContent = 'Copied — paste into your AI';
        btn.disabled = true;
        setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = original; btn.disabled = false; }, 2600);
      } catch {
        window.open(btn.dataset.src || '/context.txt', '_blank');
      }
    });
  }
</script>

<style>
  #copy-spec { font-family: inherit; }
</style>

<style>
  /* ─── layout wrapper ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

  /* ─── hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .hero {
    padding: 8rem 0 7rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5.5vw, 4.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.06;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
  }

  .hero .hl { color: var(--accent); }

  .desktop-break { display: none; }
  @media (min-width: 769px) { .desktop-break { display: block; } }

  .hero .lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero .audience {
    margin-top: 1.8rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ─── label (eyebrow / section tag) ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .label {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* ─── couplet ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .couplet {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    max-width: 680px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 2.4rem;
  }
  .couplet .a { color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .couplet .b { display: block; color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ─── spec strip ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .spec-strip {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
  }
  .spec-strip .wrap {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .spec-strip .sep { color: var(--border); user-select: none; }
  .spec-strip strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
  .spec-strip a { color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .spec-strip a:hover { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }

  /* ─── section layout ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .sec { padding: 6rem 0; }
  .sec + .sec { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .sec-alt { background: var(--bg-elevated); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }

  /* ─── section heading pattern ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .sec h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3.2vw, 2.6rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }
  .sec .body-lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .sec p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .sec p strong { color: var(--text-primary); }
  .sec p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ─── invariant / receipt layout ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .invariant-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 0.95fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .invariant-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  }

  /* receipt — the one monospace element */
  .receipt {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
  }
  .receipt-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
  }
  .receipt-tag {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .receipt-fields {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-main);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }
  .rf-key  { color: var(--text-tertiary); white-space: nowrap; }
  .rf-val  { color: var(--text-primary); word-break: break-all; }
  .rf-note { color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 0.75rem; }

  /* numbered causal chain */
  .chain { list-style: none; counter-reset: c; padding: 0.4rem 0 0; margin: 0; }
  .chain li {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 0 1.4rem 2.4rem;
    counter-increment: c;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .chain li::before {
    content: counter(c);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.05rem;
    width: 1.65rem;
    height: 1.65rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: var(--bg-main);
  }
  .chain li::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0.8rem;
    top: 1.75rem;
    bottom: 0.05rem;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }
  .chain li:last-child::after { display: none; }
  .chain li:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
  .chain .role  { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .chain strong { color: var(--text-primary); }

  /* neutrality note */
  .neutrality {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .neutrality strong { color: var(--text-secondary); }

  /* ─── contrast table ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  table.contrast {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    max-width: 760px;
    /* override global.css table rules */
    display: table;
    overflow-x: visible;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    table-layout: fixed;
  }
  table.contrast th,
  table.contrast td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.8rem 1rem;
    border: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    background: transparent;
    /* override global mobile rule that sets white-space: nowrap */
    white-space: normal;
    word-break: break-word;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    table.contrast th, table.contrast td { padding: 0.6rem 0.6rem; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  }
  table.contrast thead th {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  table.contrast td.hap { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
  table.contrast td.old { color: var(--text-secondary); }
  /* kill global alternating row bg on contrast tables */
  table.contrast tr:nth-child(even) { background: transparent; }

  /* ─── Article 14 note ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .a14 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .a14 .label { color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .a14 p { color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .a14 .caveat {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ─── commitment modes ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .modes { margin-top: 2.4rem; max-width: 820px; }
  .modes > div {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.4rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .modes > div:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .mode-name { font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.3; }
  .mode-name .who {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
  }
  .modes p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .modes p strong { color: var(--text-primary); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .modes > div { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }

  /* ─── soul line ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .soul {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    max-width: 680px;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0;
    /* override .sec p margin */
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  /* ─── use cases / building blocks grid ───────────────────────────────── */
  .usecases {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2.2rem;
    max-width: 860px;
  }
  .usecases > div {
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .usecases > div span {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .usecases { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 440px) { .usecases { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  /* ─── CTA group (homepage — left-aligned) ─────────────────────────────── */
  .cta-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>
